WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:04.730
Prof: Okay,
let's start up.

00:00:04.730 --> 00:00:08.960
So last time we got to the
point of asking the question,

00:00:08.960 --> 00:00:11.430
are there atoms and molecules
-- and well,

00:00:11.430 --> 00:00:14.890
I anticipate that the answer is
yes --

00:00:14.890 --> 00:00:17.370
and what force holds the atoms
together?

00:00:17.370 --> 00:00:22.310
Because if we really understand
the force that holds them,

00:00:22.310 --> 00:00:25.170
we've got chemistry all solved.
 

00:00:25.170 --> 00:00:29.919
So when you come to the idea of
forces, in the first place,

00:00:29.919 --> 00:00:34.750
one goes back to Newton and
Principia Mathematica.

00:00:34.750 --> 00:00:38.145
And he had the idea,
or developed the idea,

00:00:38.145 --> 00:00:40.490
the mathematics of gravity.
 

00:00:40.490 --> 00:00:44.185
And the interesting thing about
it was there was no mechanism

00:00:44.185 --> 00:00:44.740
for it.
 

00:00:44.740 --> 00:00:47.943
There were no springs or
strings that connected the

00:00:47.943 --> 00:00:48.520
things.
 

00:00:48.520 --> 00:00:51.720
It was action at a distance.
 

00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:53.670
So there were other ideas.
 

00:00:53.670 --> 00:00:57.817
Like, Descartes had the idea
that gravity resulted from

00:00:57.817 --> 00:01:01.075
blocked repulsion,
that the universe was full of

00:01:01.075 --> 00:01:03.798
particles zipping around and
bombarding things.

00:01:03.798 --> 00:01:07.558
So like the moon would be
bombarded by particles from all

00:01:07.558 --> 00:01:11.516
directions, but there'd be no
net force on it because they'd

00:01:11.516 --> 00:01:12.860
all balance out.
 

00:01:12.860 --> 00:01:17.256
However, if you put the earth
in the way, there'd be a shadow,

00:01:17.256 --> 00:01:21.652
and now you'd have more things
hitting the moon from the right

00:01:21.652 --> 00:01:23.310
than from the left.
 

00:01:23.310 --> 00:01:27.549
So it would seem to be
attracted to the earth.

00:01:27.549 --> 00:01:30.780
So that's a great mechanism.
 

00:01:30.780 --> 00:01:36.839
Now, it was important for
Newton that the force be

00:01:36.839 --> 00:01:42.280
proportional to r^2,
to inverse r^2,1/r^2.

00:01:42.280 --> 00:01:44.450
Does this work for that?
 

00:01:44.450 --> 00:01:50.800
If you pulled the earth back,
how would you change things?

00:01:50.800 --> 00:01:51.440
What do you say?
 

00:01:51.440 --> 00:01:53.030
Student:  I don't know.
 

00:01:53.030 --> 00:01:53.860
It doesn't work for this.
 

00:01:53.860 --> 00:01:56.209
Prof: It doesn't work?
 

00:01:56.209 --> 00:01:59.599
Would it block more or fewer
things if you pulled it back?

00:01:59.599 --> 00:02:00.879
Students:  Fewer.
 

00:02:00.879 --> 00:02:03.030
Prof: How many fewer?
 

00:02:03.030 --> 00:02:06.727
Suppose you made it twice as
far back, how many fewer would

00:02:06.727 --> 00:02:08.960
be blocked from hitting the
moon?

00:02:08.960 --> 00:02:13.409
Student:  Wouldn't it be
r^2?

00:02:13.409 --> 00:02:15.819
Prof: It would be 1/r^2.
 

00:02:15.819 --> 00:02:17.620
You can think about that.
 

00:02:17.620 --> 00:02:19.938
So that aspect of it would work.
 

00:02:19.938 --> 00:02:23.003
How about -- you know gravity
is proportional to the mass of

00:02:23.003 --> 00:02:23.680
the things.
 

00:02:23.680 --> 00:02:25.560
How does that figure?
 

00:02:25.560 --> 00:02:28.520
You can think about that
yourselves, okay?

00:02:28.520 --> 00:02:30.068
But anyhow, there were other
ideas.

00:02:30.068 --> 00:02:33.444
But Newton didn't think about
the mechanism,

00:02:33.444 --> 00:02:37.056
he thought about the law,
that it was 1/r^2 and

00:02:37.056 --> 00:02:39.490
proportional to the masses.
 

00:02:39.490 --> 00:02:44.532
Now in 1717,
he published the Second Edition

00:02:44.532 --> 00:02:46.878
of Opticks.
 

00:02:46.878 --> 00:02:51.663
He published the First Edition
in 1704, and the reason he

00:02:51.663 --> 00:02:56.620
published it in 1704 was that
Robert Hooke died in 1703.

00:02:56.620 --> 00:03:01.812
He'd actually -- Newton had
done this work in the 1660s and

00:03:01.812 --> 00:03:04.358
'70s,
but he didn't publish it until

00:03:04.358 --> 00:03:07.893
Hooke died because he didn't
want Hooke to get on his case,

00:03:07.893 --> 00:03:08.990
criticizing it.
 

00:03:08.990 --> 00:03:12.383
But in the Second Edition,
in 1717, he put some additional

00:03:12.383 --> 00:03:14.468
material;
you see, "with Additions.

00:03:14.468 --> 00:03:17.502
" And the additional
material, even though the book

00:03:17.502 --> 00:03:19.817
is about optics,
the additional material is

00:03:19.817 --> 00:03:20.919
about chemistry.
 

00:03:20.919 --> 00:03:27.215
And it's at the end,
and posed not as hypotheses but

00:03:27.215 --> 00:03:30.913
as questions,
because Baconian people,

00:03:30.913 --> 00:03:34.504
following Francis Bacon,
weren't supposed to make

00:03:34.504 --> 00:03:37.160
hypotheses,
but they could ask questions.

00:03:37.160 --> 00:03:39.430
So here are some of the
questions.

00:03:39.430 --> 00:03:42.111
Question thirty-one,
the one that has most to do

00:03:42.111 --> 00:03:44.446
with chemistry:
"Have not the small

00:03:44.446 --> 00:03:46.460
Particles of Bodies certain
Powers,

00:03:46.460 --> 00:03:52.520
Virtues, or Forces by which
they act at a distance,

00:03:52.520 --> 00:03:55.180
not only on the Rays of Light
to reflect,

00:03:55.180 --> 00:03:58.912
refract and inflect them,
but also upon one another for

00:03:58.912 --> 00:04:02.990
producing a great part of the
Phaenomena of Nature?"

00:04:02.990 --> 00:04:06.521
(And this attraction between
the particles or repulsion)

00:04:06.521 --> 00:04:10.375
"For it's well known that
Bodies act upon one another by

00:04:10.375 --> 00:04:14.098
the Attractions of Gravity,
Magnetism and Electricity;

00:04:14.098 --> 00:04:17.689
and these Instances shew the
Tenor and Course of Nature,

00:04:17.689 --> 00:04:21.084
and make it not improbable but
that there may be more

00:04:21.084 --> 00:04:23.240
attractive Powers than these.
 

00:04:23.240 --> 00:04:27.939
For Nature is very consonant
and conformable to her self.

00:04:27.939 --> 00:04:33.238
How these Attractions may be
perform'd, I do not here

00:04:33.238 --> 00:04:34.360
consider.
 

00:04:34.360 --> 00:04:36.851
What I call Attraction may be
perform'd by

00:04:36.851 --> 00:04:42.870
impulse…"
Where did he get that idea?

00:04:42.870 --> 00:04:45.899
Where did he get the idea that
there are impulses that can

00:04:45.899 --> 00:04:46.910
cause attraction?
 

00:04:46.910 --> 00:04:49.879
Student:
&gt;

00:04:49.879 --> 00:04:53.168
Prof: That was
Descartes' idea,

00:04:53.168 --> 00:04:55.389
that we just explained.
 

00:04:55.389 --> 00:04:57.959
"…or by some other
means unknown to me.

00:04:57.959 --> 00:05:02.670
I use that Word here to signify
only in general any Force by

00:05:02.670 --> 00:05:06.980
which Bodies tend toward one
another, whatsoever be the

00:05:06.980 --> 00:05:07.778
Cause.
 

00:05:07.778 --> 00:05:12.562
For we must learn from the
Phaenomena of Nature what Bodies

00:05:12.562 --> 00:05:16.382
attract one another,
and what are the Laws and

00:05:16.382 --> 00:05:20.581
Properties of attraction,
before we enquire the Cause by

00:05:20.581 --> 00:05:23.480
which the Attraction is
perform'd."

00:05:23.480 --> 00:05:27.336
(So get the law first so you
can do mathematics on it,

00:05:27.336 --> 00:05:30.028
and then worry about how it
works.)

00:05:30.028 --> 00:05:32.994
"The Attractions of
Gravity, Magnetism and

00:05:32.994 --> 00:05:36.732
Electricity, react to very
sensible distances…"

00:05:36.732 --> 00:05:40.211
(He doesn't mean reasonable,
he means ones that you can

00:05:40.211 --> 00:05:41.050
sense.)
 

00:05:41.050 --> 00:05:44.560
"…and so have been
observed by vulgar Eyes."

00:05:44.560 --> 00:05:49.995
(You can see the distances over
which electrostatic attraction

00:05:49.995 --> 00:05:53.470
works, obviously gravity,
magnetism.)

00:05:53.470 --> 00:05:57.492
"And there may be others
which reach to so small

00:05:57.492 --> 00:06:01.050
distances as hitherto to escape
observation;

00:06:01.050 --> 00:06:04.053
and perhaps electrical
Attraction may reach to such

00:06:04.053 --> 00:06:06.757
small distances,
even without being excited by

00:06:06.757 --> 00:06:07.899
Friction."
 

00:06:07.899 --> 00:06:10.918
(So you know that friction can
generate static electricity

00:06:10.918 --> 00:06:14.935
that'll make things attract,
but maybe even without friction

00:06:14.935 --> 00:06:19.382
you can get things that'll
attract a very short distance by

00:06:19.382 --> 00:06:20.610
electricity.)
 

00:06:20.610 --> 00:06:23.886
"The Parts of all
homogeneal hard Bodies which

00:06:23.886 --> 00:06:26.704
fully touch one another,
stick together very

00:06:26.704 --> 00:06:27.949
strongly."
 

00:06:27.949 --> 00:06:31.848
Did you ever have that
experience of having two really

00:06:31.848 --> 00:06:36.113
flat things, put them together
and they're very hard to get

00:06:36.113 --> 00:06:37.860
apart;
what?

00:06:37.860 --> 00:06:39.129
Student: Slides.
 

00:06:39.129 --> 00:06:39.850
Student:  Small things.
 

00:06:39.850 --> 00:06:40.850
Prof: Microscope slides.
 

00:06:40.850 --> 00:06:42.949
Ever take out new microscope
slides?

00:06:42.949 --> 00:06:45.180
They can be very hard to get
apart.

00:06:45.180 --> 00:06:49.483
"And for explaining how
this may be, some have invented

00:06:49.483 --> 00:06:52.839
hooked Atoms,
which is begging the Question;

00:06:52.839 --> 00:06:56.139
and others tell us that Bodies
are glued together by rest,

00:06:56.139 --> 00:07:00.410
that is, by an occult Quality,
or rather by nothing,

00:07:00.410 --> 00:07:03.439
and others that they stick
together by conspiring motions,

00:07:03.439 --> 00:07:06.079
that is by relative rest among
themselves."

00:07:06.079 --> 00:07:08.230
(These are other theories that
are sort of complicated;

00:07:08.230 --> 00:07:10.899
we don't need to go into it.)
 

00:07:10.899 --> 00:07:14.750
"I had rather infer from
their Cohesion,

00:07:14.750 --> 00:07:19.350
that their Particles attract
one another by some Force,

00:07:19.350 --> 00:07:24.060
which in immediate Contact is
exceeding strong,

00:07:24.060 --> 00:07:28.004
at small distances performs the
chymical Operations above

00:07:28.004 --> 00:07:31.163
mention'd,
and reaches not far from the

00:07:31.163 --> 00:07:34.529
Particles with any sensible
Effect."

00:07:34.529 --> 00:07:39.670
(So a very short-range,
a very strong attraction.)

00:07:39.670 --> 00:07:43.281
"…reaches not far
from the Particles with any

00:07:43.281 --> 00:07:44.829
sensible Effect."
 

00:07:44.829 --> 00:07:49.230
So maybe it's even more
dramatic than 1/r^2.^( )1/r^2

00:07:49.230 --> 00:07:53.209
changes very rapidly when r gets
very small,

00:07:53.209 --> 00:07:56.500
but maybe it's even a law
that's more distance dependant

00:07:56.500 --> 00:07:58.447
than that,
but only works at really,

00:07:58.447 --> 00:07:59.569
really small distances.
 

00:07:59.569 --> 00:08:03.492
"The Attraction"
(and he's talking about between

00:08:03.492 --> 00:08:07.759
glass plates separated by a thin
film of the Oil of Oranges;

00:08:07.759 --> 00:08:09.394
so you know,
microscope slides,

00:08:09.394 --> 00:08:12.062
they put a little drop of
something and stick them

00:08:12.062 --> 00:08:15.221
together and they're really hard
to get apart) "may be

00:08:15.221 --> 00:08:18.163
proportionally greater"
